<toc-add-entry name="outside">Outside News</toc-add-entry>

<p>At the 2016 <a href="http://www.opencompute.org/">Open Compute Project</a> 
summit, Microsoft released <a href="http://azure.github.io/SONiC/">SONiC</a>, a 
Debian based software platform that uses the <a href="https://github.com/opencomputeproject/SAI">Switch Abstraction 
Interface</a> (SAI) to allow network administrators to control network devices 
with customised configurations and controls.</p> 

<p>Earlier this year we reported on Microsoft in collaboration with credativ 
adding Debian to its list of <a
href="https://azure.microsoft.com/ja-jp/blog/debian-images-now-available-on-azure/"><q>endorsed
distributions</q></a> for its Azure marketplace.</p>


